pageContext.claim: ““The lowest average jobs number for any President since 1951, 4.1%. Economy doing great. If the Democrats win, it is all over.” @Varneyco  @foxandfriends  I agree!”
pageContext.analysis: What exactly Trump is referencing isn't clear, but 4.1 percent is not the lowest annual unemployment rate and that the economy is shaped by broad economic trends so no matter who is the next president may face a tough economic situation because the economy has expanded for so long.
